docs/architecture.md:25:`compat/runner/src/layout.rs` is the central resolver for client, server, and compatibility roots. It uses canonical role-based paths for active defaults and fails closed with migration diagnostics for old transition roots, missing required roots, ambiguous duplicate roots, or nested Git directories inside core component trees.
cairn/changes/retire-layout-transition-paths/proposal.md:1:# Proposal: Retire legacy layout transition paths
cairn/changes/retire-layout-transition-paths/proposal.md:5:`compat/runner/src/layout.rs` still accepts both role-based paths and older transition paths. That was useful during migration, but long-term dual layouts add ambiguity and increase the chance that tooling probes the wrong component root. Once current users are migrated, the workspace should prefer one canonical path per role.
cairn/changes/retire-layout-transition-paths/proposal.md:9:- Inventory every transition path currently accepted by layout resolution and any command, doc, or evidence reference that still uses it.
cairn/changes/retire-layout-transition-paths/design.md:1:# Design: Retire legacy layout transition paths
cairn/changes/retire-layout-transition-paths/design.md:5:The resolver supports role paths such as `clients/stevenarella` and legacy transition paths such as direct root-level component names. Dual support makes ambiguity checks necessary and keeps old names alive in docs and tests.
